Whether a void should be shown in responding to Blackwood is a point that is often argued. Some experts with the North hand would bid six diamonds directly, promising one ace and a void in diamonds. This would have prevented South from inquiring about kings and might have prevented a debacle for the defenders.|
PG| ***** 9 ***** |


